class Solution {
    public int latestTimeCatchTheBus(int[] buses, int[] passengers, int capacity) {
        Arrays.sort(buses);
        Arrays.sort(passengers);
        int result = buses[passengers.length];
        for (int i = 0; i < passengers.length; i++) {
            if (passengers[i] <= buses[result]) {
                result = Math.min(result, passengers[i]);
            }
        }
        return result - 1;
    }
}
```

efficiency:

Efficiency: HIGH
Time complexity: O(n) (where n is the length of the buses array)
Space complexity: O(1) (constant space complexity)
Energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

1. Sort both buses and passengers arrays to ensure comparing elements in sorted order.
2. Initialize result variable with the last index of buses array (buses.length).
3. Iterate through the passengers array and update result if the current passenger's arrival time is less than or equal to the current bus's departure time.
4. Return result - 1 to account for the initial bus departure time.

